  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Cholangitis is the most prevalent infectious complication of ERCP. Stenting of biliary
      strictures and stenosis is one of important risk factors for post-ERCP cholangitis. Adding
      antibiotics to contrast media has proposed in some studies for prevention of cholangitis but
      remains controversial. In this study we compare effect of adding gentamicin versus placebo in
      preventing cholangitis in patients who undergone endoscopic stenting for non-calculus
      strictures and stenosis.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
